 }}
 {{Politics of Ukraine}}
-The '''Act of Declaration of Independence of Ukraine''' ({{lang-uk|Акт проголошеньня незалежності України}}, [[Romanization of Ukrainian|translit.]] ''Akt proholoshen'nya nezalezhnosti Ukrayini'') was adopted by the [[Verkhovna Rada|Ukrainian parliament]] on August 24, 1991. The Act established [[Ukraine]] as an independent, democratic state.  
+The '''Act of Declaration of Independence of Ukraine''' ({{lang-uk|Акт проголошення незалежності України}}, [[Romanization of Ukrainian|translit.]] ''Akt proholoshen'nya nezalezhnosti Ukrayini'') was adopted by the [[Verkhovna Rada|Ukrainian parliament]] on August 24, 1991. The Act established [[Ukraine]] as an independent, democratic state.  

 The Act was adopted in the aftermath of the [[Soviet coup attempt of 1991|August 19th coup attempt]] when conservative Communist leaders of the [[Soviet Union]] tried to restore [[Communist Party of the Soviet Union|central Communist party]] control over the USSR.  In response, the parliament of the [[Ukrainian Soviet Socialist Republic|Ukrainian SSR]] in a special Sunday session overwhelmingly approved the Act of Declaration. The Act passed with 321 votes in favor, 2 votes against, and 6 [[abstention]]s. The author of the text was [[Levko Lukyanenko]].

